Continental, ThyssenKrupp, Volkswagen: German Equity Preview

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-05-13T04:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/continental-thyssenkrupp-volkswagen-german-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in  Germany . Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close.  Germany’s benchmark DAX index slipped 0.7 percent to
7,443.95.  Continental AG (CON)  : The tire and auto parts maker
plans to invest more than 1 billion euros in its tire business
in the coming years, particularly in emerging markets,
Handelsblatt said, citing comments from board member Nikolai
Setzer. Continental shares gained 0.4 percent to 67.46 euros.  Pfleiderer AG (PFD4 GY): The wood and infrastructure
manufacturer reached a deal with its creditors in which the
creditors waive claims worth about 380 million euros and provide
Pfleiderer with an additional credit line of 100 million euros.
The company’s shares fell 1.4 percent to 70 euro cents.  ThyssenKrupp AG (TKA)  : The steelmaker wants to maintain
a role in its stainless steel business and may float it on the
stock market rather than sell it, Handelsblatt said, citing an
agreement between management and employee representatives. The
shares retreated 1.1 percent to 32.73 euros.  Volkswagen AG (VOW)  : The carmaker may invest in offshore
wind parks, Financial Times Deutschland reported, without saying
where it got the information. Volkswagen shares slipped 0.8
percent to 118 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 